My favorite place for hookah! They pretty much always get my flavors right (and there's a huge variety). If there's ever an issue with it, it gets fixed asap. It's great to just come to chill, game, study, etc. Food has immensely improved over the last year and it's really good (quesadillas and sandwiches a must try). Staff is chill af and fun and music caters to the variety of customers that hang there. Favorite place to go hands down, really recommend. Not the spot to go if you're looking to party or drink.

Best local spot, theres so many hookah places around but this place is catered to a more "frequent" crowd No immature kids or music blasting. Just a chill lounge with quality and affordable hookahs. When theres big events like football, basketball or event UFC fights, this place gets so crowded there isnt even a place a stand !

Local spot. Super chill and this guy is playing DotA, smoking and drinking his tea next to me. How cool is that!!  I think it's my third time here. Everytime I play a new board games. You can pick up some classic and it's not idea spot to play seven wonder but of course you can and have to bring it too. Everytime the same is the quality hookah and they change the coal pretty often. Wide selection and strong flavor with the great price. I don't remember how much they charge anymore but it's pretty decent.  Usually I would go for a selection of tea for the table, a small snack and hookah. You can walk away pretty cheaply that way.  Best part is everyone here are local. It does feel like being in another country but still in Brooklyn. I dont think food is a big thing here that's why i always go here after a meal. It's more chill and play a game or two.  Explore and learn a new board game.

This is not a loud music teen filled lounge. There are no dimmed lights and LEDs here. This is just like a second home. Hookah is cheap and usually good. You'll enjoy your time.
